Goetz was nabbed in a sting operation in
Union Square park Friday evening for selling $30 worth of marijuana to 
an undercover officer, police said.

He asked the woman if she wanted to get 
high, then went back to his apartment, where he has lived for decades, 
and returned with marijuana, authorities said. He was arrested on 
charges of criminal sale of marijuana.

According to The Post, Goetz was arrested on the street at about 5.45pm after getting into conversation with the police officer.

A police source said: 'He told her he wanted to get high with her and sold her a small amount of pot in a tissue.'

